subSubSection.paragraph:
Telson (
Fig. 4
): Pre-anal ring dorsally with a few short setae; epiproct absent; hypoproct short and broadly rounded, tightly fitting under paraprocts in both sexes, with a pair of disto-median setae and a transverse row of around 10 setae proximally to the former. Paraprocts densely covered with long setae, without rows of short and stiff setae along caudal margins.

